<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7198&amp;p=70845#p70845"><![CDATA[
So the real resolution is exactly 35/32 times the amount of visible pixels?<br /><br />256 onscreen pixels:<br />32 8x8 cells<br />280 pixels<br />3.58 Mhz * 3 / 2<br />dithered artifact: 6 pixel long rainbow<br /><br />320 onscreen pixels:<br />40 8x8 cells<br />350 pixels<br />3.58 Mhz * 15 / 8<br />dithered artifact: 30 pixel long ranibow <br /><br />336 (341.67) onscreen pixels:<br />42 8x8 cells<br />373.33 pixels<br />3.58 * 2<br />dithered artifact: solid color<br /><br />384 onscreen pixels:<br />48 8x8 cells<br />460 pixels<br />3.58 * 9 / 4<br />dithered artifact: 18 pixel long rainbow<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4383">psycopathicteen</a> — Wed Dec 01, 2010 11:18 am</p><hr />
