<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7198&amp;p=70555#p70555"><![CDATA[
Because there are 480-486 visible lines on an ideal display. (Forgetting overscan.)<br /><br />It's variable. Some have better DSP than others, the technical specs aren't available to consumers. Since most HDTV sets also have analog component inputs, which operate up to 720p (pixel clock of nearly 70 MHz), hopefully a HDTV can greatly oversample a SD signal.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20">kyuusaku</a> — Fri Nov 26, 2010 4:41 pm</p><hr />
